<div class="grid-container grid-x body-content">
	<div class="cell large-9 small-12 main-content-well">
		<div class="story-content">
							<div class="story-info">
			<div class="featured-img-container">
			<img class="story-img" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-20-at-9.30.45-AM-726x400.png" title="George Saunders, Heather Ann Thompson, Stephen Fishbach, and more: 20 new books out today!">
								</div>
		<div class="story-heads">
		<h1>George Saunders, Heather Ann Thompson, Stephen Fishbach, and more: 20 new books out today!</h1>
			</div>
	</div>
										<div class="byline-date">
					<span class="byline"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/juliahass/"  title="Julia Hass">Julia Hass</a></span>
					<span class="hr"></span>
					<span class="date">January 27, 2026</span>
				</div>
						<div class="story-body">
								<p>A new George Saunders out today: what more could anyone possibly want? And yet, that&#8217;s just the beginning of our week&#8217;s delivery of thrilling new titles: there&#8217;s another rigorous and deeply investigated work about the Bernie Goetz subway shootings, a collection of stories by Camille Bordas, poems by Caleb Femi, and so much more. Happy reading, and happy Tuesday!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264380" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/george-saunders-vigil/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="George Saunders, Vigil" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264380" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-199x300.jpg" alt="George Saunders, Vigil" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/George-Saunders-Vigil.jpg 993w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>George Saunders, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780525509622" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Vigil</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Random House)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“Saunders makes the all-but-impossible look effortless.”<br />
<em>–</em>Jonathan Franzen</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264407" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/heather-ann-thompson-fear-and-fury-the-reagan-eighties-the-bernie-goetz-shootings-and-the-rebirth-of-white-rage/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Heather Ann Thompson, Fear and Fury- The Reagan Eighties, the Bernie Goetz Shootings, and the Rebirth of White Rage" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-674x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264407" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-197x300.jpg" alt="Heather Ann Thompson, Fear and Fury: The Reagan Eighties, the Bernie Goetz Shootings, and the Rebirth of White Rage" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Heather-Ann-Thompson-Fear-and-Fury-The-Reagan-Eighties-the-Bernie-Goetz-Shootings-and-the-Rebirth-of-White-Rage.jpg 987w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Heather Ann Thompson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593702093" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Fear and Fury: The Reagan Eighties, the Bernie Goetz Shootings, and the Rebirth of White Rage</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Pantheon)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A comprehensive account of a vicious outburst that shook New York four decades ago.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265620" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/attachment/9780593729878/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878.jpeg" data-orig-size="300,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="One Sun Only Camille Bordas" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265620" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878-200x300.jpeg" alt="One Sun Only Camille Bordas" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593729878.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Camille Bordas, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593729878" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>One Sun Only: Stories</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Random House)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;The prose is exact, unshowy, funny when it hurts to be, and tender without asking for mercy. These stories don’t close so much as continue inside you.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Morgan Talty</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265619" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/images-118/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/images-1.jpeg" data-orig-size="180,279" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Summer My Mother Had Green Eyes" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/images-1.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/images-1.jpeg" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-265619" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/images-1.jpeg" alt="The Summer My Mother Had Green Eyes" width="180" height="279" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/images-1.jpeg 180w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/images-1-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/images-1-32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 180px) 100vw, 180px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Tatiana Țîbuleac, trans. by Monica Cure, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781646054107" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Summer My Mother Had Green Eyes</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Deep Vellum)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A wryly tender exploration of grief, rage, and the fraught process of repairing a broken parent-child relationship.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264378" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/stephen-fishbach-escape/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Stephen Fishbach, Escape!" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-683x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264378" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-200x300.jpg" alt="Stephen Fishbach, Escape!" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephen-Fishbach-Escape.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stephen Fishbach, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9798217048151" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Escape!</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Dutton)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“Stephen Fishbach writes with great energy and humor, as well as a deep understanding of human longing.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Jonathan Safran Foer</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265621" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/attachment/9780593655870/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870.jpeg" data-orig-size="298,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Until the Last Gun is Silent" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265621" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870-199x300.jpeg" alt="Until the Last Gun is Silent" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593655870.jpeg 298w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Matthew F. Delmont, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593655870" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Until the Last Gun is Silent: A Story of Patriotism, the Vietnam War, and the Fight to Save America&#8217;s Soul</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Viking)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Meticulously researched and beautifully written &#8230; With masterful storytelling and graceful prose.&#8221;<br />
<em>–BookPage</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265622" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/attachment/9780593594179/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179.jpeg" data-orig-size="298,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Neptune&#8217;s Fortune" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265622" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179-199x300.jpeg" alt="Neptune's Fortune" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/9780593594179.jpeg 298w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Julian Sancton, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593594179" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Neptune&#8217;s Fortune: The Billion-Dollar Shipwreck and the Ghosts of the Spanish Empire</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Crown)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A deeply reported adventure, a study in obsession, and a thoroughly engrossing read.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Susan Orlean</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264379" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/alice-evelyn-yang-a-beast-slinks-towards-beijing/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Alice Evelyn Yang, A Beast Slinks Towards Beijing" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264379" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-199x300.jpg" alt="Alice Evelyn Yang, A Beast Slinks Towards Beijing" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alice-Evelyn-Yang-A-Beast-Slinks-Towards-Beijing.jpg 993w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Alice Evelyn Yang, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780063419292" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Beast Slinks Towards Beijing</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(William Morrow)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A deftly rendered, engrossing multigenerational work of magical realism that integrates 20th-century Chinese history, complex family ties, and lingering traumas.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Library Journal</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265405" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=265405" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1656,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="beckomberga" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-663x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265405" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-194x300.jpg" alt="beckomberga" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-663x1024.jpg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-768x1187.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-994x1536.jpg 994w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-1325x2048.jpg 1325w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/beckomberga-scaled.jpg 1656w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></p>
