<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>William J. Mann, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668075906" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Black Dahlia: Murder, Monsters, and Madness in Midcentury Hollywood</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Simon and Schuster)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A meticulous and humane reconsideration of one of America’s most sensationalized unsolved murders &#8230; Mann sets out to restore complexity and dignity to a woman long reduced to tabloid caricature.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265629" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/81x2zpqfwil-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="709,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Winter Warriors" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-213x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265629" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-213x300.jpg" alt="The Winter Warriors" width="213" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-213x300.jpg 213w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-43x60.jpg 43w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-35x50.jpg 35w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/81x2ZPQfwiL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 709w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 213px) 100vw, 213px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Olivier Norek, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780802167651" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Winter Warriors</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Atlantic Monthly)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Timely, thrilling, and deeply affecting &#8230; [A] tour de force.&#8221;<br />
<em>–The Independent</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264376" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/emi-yagi-tr-yuki-tejima-when-the-museum-is-closed/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed.jpg" data-orig-size="938,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Emi Yagi, tr. Yuki Tejima, When the Museum is Closed" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-640x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264376" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-188x300.jpg" alt="Emi Yagi, tr. Yuki Tejima, When the Museum is Closed" width="188" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-640x1024.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-768x1228.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emi-Yagi-tr.-Yuki-Tejima-When-the-Museum-is-Closed.jpg 938w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 188px) 100vw, 188px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Emi Yagi, trans. by Yuki Tejima, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781593768270" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>When the Museum is Closed</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Soft Skull)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Yagi’s characters and the world they inhabit are as inimitably charming as they are whimsical &#8230; A magical love story couched in absurdist fabulism.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265632" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/71t5y6l2ozl-_ac_uf350350_ql50_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_.jpg" data-orig-size="231,350" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="After the Flood, Robert Polito" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265632" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_-198x300.jpg" alt="After the Flood, Robert Polito" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/71t5y6l2OzL._AC_UF350350_QL50_.jpg 231w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Robert Polito, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780871402936" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>After the Flood: Inside Bob Dylan&#8217;s Memory Palace</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Liveright)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Encyclopedic yet concise, it is an ideal listening companion and a definitive guide to Dylan&#8217;s many reinvention.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Lucy Sante</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265639" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2159" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="In Bloom, Liz Allan" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-664x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265639" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-195x300.jpg" alt="In Bloom, Liz Allan " width="195" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-768x1184.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-996x1536.jpg 996w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-1328x2048.jpg 1328w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/in-bloom-9781668205938_hr.jpg 1400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 195px) 100vw, 195px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Liz Allan, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668205938" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>In Bloom</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Simon and Schuster)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A smart look at teen culture, the inner workings of status, and the importance of true friendship. If ever there was a book to which one could consider head banging, this might be it.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Town and Country</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="265633" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/george-saunders-heather-ann-thompson-stephen-fishbach-and-more-20-new-books-out-today/screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1-02-49-pm/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM.png" data-orig-size="964,1448" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Hated By All the Right People" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-200x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-682x1024.png" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-265633" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-200x300.png" alt="Hated By All the Right People" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-200x300.png 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-682x1024.png 682w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-768x1154.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-40x60.png 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM-33x50.png 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-15-at-1.02.49-PM.png 964w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Jason Zengerle, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781638932932" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Hated By All the Right People: Tucker Carlson and the Unraveling of the Conservative Mind</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Crooked Media Reads)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A riveting, wry, disturbing portrait of the man who made the Trump Age possible.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Jon Favreau</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264377" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/aoife-josie-clements-persona/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona.jpg" data-orig-size="844,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Aoife Josie Clements, Persona" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-169x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-576x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264377" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-169x300.jpg" alt="Aoife Josie Clements, Persona" width="169" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-169x300.jpg 169w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-576x1024.jpg 576w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-768x1365.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-34x60.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona-28x50.jpg 28w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Aoife-Josie-Clements-Persona.jpg 844w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 169px) 100vw, 169px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Aoife Josie Clements, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781964322063" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Persona</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Littlepuss Press)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A nightmarishly realistic and immersively terrifying journey, forcing the reader to take a long, hard look at late-stage capitalism, internet obsession, even what it means to be human.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
